article.headline: West Virginia 95, Maryland-Eastern Shore 49
article.story: MORGANTOWN, W.Va. (AP) -- Five West Virginia players, led by Frank Young, scored in double-digits as the Mountaineers beat Maryland-Eastern Shore 95-49 on Thursday night. Young scored 16 points and was 4-of-8 from 3-point range. West Virginia (10-1) hit 12-of-24 3-pointers overall. It was the eighth game this season that the Mountaineers hit more than 10 from 3-point range. West Virginia limited the Hawks to two 3-pointers. Joe Alexander scored six of his 14 points in the opening six minutes to give West Virginia a 12-0 lead and the Mountaineers never trailed. West Virginia led 47-23 at half time. Wellington Smith scored West Virginia's final 10 points, giving him a career high of 12 points. Rob Summers and Joe Mazzulla each scored career highs also, with 12 and 9 points respectively. Ed Tyson led Maryland-Eastern Shore (2-9) with 13 points. Antonio McMillion and Corey Brown each scored 11 points for the Hawks. Thursday's game marked the first meeting between the schools. West Virginia is 6-0 at home this season.
